        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nShortness of breath and chest pain.\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports feeling out of breath with exertion and experiencing slight chest pain, particularly with activity. He states the chest pain has been present for approximately two weeks and is rated as 4/10. He reports a history of heart failure and currently takes Bumex 2 milligrams once daily, cozaar, and norvasc. He also reports ankle swelling and difficulty eating anything, including salty foods. The patient reports eating chips today. He denies recent trauma. He reports taking a multivitamin as recommended by his doctor.\nFindings\nThe patient's blood pressure is 142/88 mmHg. The patient reports ankle swelling. Examination reveals no acute distress.\nAssessment\nThe patient has a history of heart failure, hypertension, and is currently experiencing shortness of breath and chest pain.\nPlan\nOrder a nutrition consult. The doctor ordered a nutrition consult. The doctor recommends seeing a nutritionist. Start Bumex 2 milligrams once daily. Follow up in four weeks if symptoms persist.",
